 the specific choice of fuel in\nthose classes mattered less than ensuring the representation of the relevant\nfunctional group. This work builds upon previous efforts by creating models\ninformed by neat and surrogate fuels---rather than complex real fuels---that\ncould predict the performance of complex unknown fuels.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 22 Jun 2016 21:49:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-07-06"}
